INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES(162, 1, '2013-04-30 07:03:52', '2013-04-30 07:03:52', '<h1>Muerte injusta</h1>\r\nSiempre que alguien cerca de nosotross muere nosotros nos sentimos triste y disgustados. Cuándo esa persona es perdida a causa de alguna persona o la negligencia de grupo, la mala conducta, o el descuidado, nuestra tristesa es aún más grande. Sabiendo que la muerte no fue necesaria, que las acciones de alguien o inacciones lo causaron, es producto de una muerte injusta.\r\n\r\nLos parientes más cercanos o la familia sobreviviente pueden archivar un reclamo de la muerte si ellos creen que la muerte resulto de la negligencia, de la mala conducta, o del descuidado. Los casos como estos son trágicamente comunes y pueden surgir de una variedad de causas. Algunos de éstos incluyen exposición innecesaria a sustancias perjudiciales como asbesto, las reacciones a Vioxxa y otras medicinas, la negligencia u otra negligencia en la parte de profesionales médicos, accidentes de automóvil que es causado por descuidado o la conducción temeraria, inclusive conductores en estado de embriaguez, y las muertes que es causado por productos defectuosos de que el fabricante supo de o debe haber sido consciente.\r\n<h3>Qué Es lo que Significa"Muerte Injusta"</h3>\r\nUna variedad de casos y muertes puede ser consideradas como una muerte injusta. En esencia, una muerte injusta es uno que es innecesario y eso sólo ocurrió a causa de la negligencia de alguien, la mala conducta, el descuidado,o por sus acciones. Una muerte injusta puede venir acerca de instantáneamente, como durante un accidente de automóvil, o lentamente, como después de exposición al asbesto.\r\n<h3>¿Qué Es Algunos Ejemplos de la Muerte Injusta?</h3>\r\nRecientemente, ha habido un número creciente de muertes del mesothelioma, un resultado de exposición de asbesto. Esta exposición puede resultar de fabricantes que pueden ser mostrados para ser negligentes o de las companías que fallan de notificara a sus trabajadores acerca de la presencia de asbesto y no proporcionar la protección adecuada contra ello.\r\n\r\nY no es justo asbesto. Las personas se mueren innecesariamente después de que sea expuesto al Benceno. La exposición a los vapores que vienen de soldar barras también puede ser un asesino, y el descuidado o la negligencia en la parte de las companías que hacen estos productos o los grupos que los utiliza también pueden tener como resultado una muerte injusta.\r\n\r\nLas companías farmacéuticas, también, pueden ser responsable de los que fueron matados utilizando sus productos, incluso si el producto fuera utilizado como dirigido. Merck, el fabricante de Vioxxa, ha sido encontrado responsable de las muertes que vinieron acerca de a causa de efectos secundario de esa droga, y de otras drogas semejantes también han sido encontradas de causar muertes.\r\n<h3>¿Qué Puedo Hacer yo Si Creo que algun miembro de su familia ha Sufrido una Muerte Injusta?</h3>\r\nLos que se quedan después de que alguien muere por causa de una muerte injusta se siente naturalmente frustrado y permitido a la compensación. La muerte es siempre un tiempo muy estresante, y si esa muerte fue innecesaria y causada por otros o por otra persona, los sentimientos son pronunciados aún más. La muerte puede crear no sólo tristeza y consternación, pero consecuencias financieras graves si la persona que se muere fue el unico cuyos ingresos sostuvieron a sufamilia.\r\n\r\nSi la muerte resultó de un accidente de tráfico, los efectos secundario de medicinas, de la negligencia, o de cualquiera de varias condiciones igualmente trágicas, los miembros restantes de la familia pueden tener derecho para recibir compensación para su pérdida innecesaria y drástica.\r\n\r\nSi usted cree que la muerte de un miembro de su familia fue el resultado de una muerte injusta, usted debe contactar A Las Officiinas de Ley de David Azizi para que uno de nuestro abogados personal experienciado de muertes injustas pueda proporcionar acción iguala a su cuidar. Representación y ayuda legales calificadas lo pueden ayudar a recibir compensación justo para su pérdida, y para ayuda a vencer su sentido de la impotencia. Una consulta inicial donde podemos discutir su caso, que reparación y la compensación legales y cómo nosotros podemos proporcionar mejor ayuda.\r\n\r\nNuestra experiencia con casos semejantes nos da una ventaja más de algunos otros abogados personales de herida. Sabemos cómo construir y presentar un caso sólido que dará a usted el arreglo mas alto posible, uno que incluya reconocimiento de su pena, el dolor y sufriendo, y consecuencias financieras.\r\n\r\nPodemos asegurarnos de que su pérdida no es peor de lo que necesita ser y que su dolor, la angustia, y la pérdida innecesaria y profunda son reconocidos y son dirigidos completamente. Nada puede reemplazar a la persona perdida o deshace la muerte innecesaria, pero podemos asegurarnos de que su sufrimiento pare allí.', 'Muerte Injusta', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'muerte-injusta', '', '', '2013-05-20 22:46:07', '2013-05-20 22:46:07', '', 0, 'http://azizipersonalinjury.com/dev/espanol/?page_id=162', 0, 'page', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES(163, 1, '2013-04-30 07:03:34', '2013-04-30 07:03:34', 'Wrongful Death\nWhenever someone close to us dies we naturally feel sad and upset. When that person is lost to us because of some person''s or group''s negligence, misconduct, or carelessness, our distress is even greater. Knowing that the death wasn''t necessary, that someone''s actions or inactions caused it, produces what is called a wrongful death.\n\nThe next of kin or surviving family may file a wrongful death lawsuit if they believe the death resulted from negligence, misconduct, or carelessness. Cases like this are tragically common and can arise from a variety of causes. Some of these include unnecessary exposure to harmful substances such as asbestos, reactions to Vioxx® and other medications, malpractice or other negligence on the part of medical professionals, automobile accidents that are caused by careless or reckless driving, including drunk drivers, and deaths that are caused by defective products that the manufacturer knew about or should have been aware of.\n\n\nWhat is Meant By “Wrongful Death?”\nA variety of cases and deaths can be considered as a wrongful death. In essence, a wrongful death is one that is unnecessary and that only occurred because of someone''s negligence, misconduct, carelessness, or by their actions. A wrongful death can come about instantly, such as during a motor vehicle accident, or slowly, like after exposure to asbestos.\n\n<h3>What Are Some Examples of Wrongful Death?</h3>\n\nRecently, there have been an increasing number of deaths from mesothelioma, a result of asbestos exposure. This exposure can result from manufacturers who can be shown to be negligent or from companies that fail to notify their workers about the presence of asbestos and do not provide adequate protection against it.\n\nAnd it isn''t just asbestos. People needlessly die after being exposed to Benzene. Exposure to the fumes that come from welding rods can also be a killer, and carelessness or negligence on the part of companies who make these products or groups who use them can also result in a wrongful death.\n\nDrug companies, too, can be liable for those who were killed by using their products, even if the product was used as directed. Merck, the manufacturer of Vioxx®, has been found responsible for deaths that came about because of side-effects of that drug, and other similar drugs have also been found to cause fatalities.\n\n<h3>What Can I Do If I Believe a Loved One Has Suffered a Wrongful Death?</h3>\n\nThose who remain after a family member has died from a wrongful death naturally feel frustrated and entitled to compensation. The loss of a loved one is always a very stressful time, and if that death was unnecessary and caused by others or another person, the feelings are even more pronounced. The death can create not only sadness and dismay, but serious financial consequences if the person who dies was the one whose income sustained the family.\n\nWhether the death resulted from exposure, a car accident, side effects from medicines, malpractice, or any one of a number of equally tragic conditions, the remaining members of the family may be entitled to receive compensation for their needless and drastic loss.\n\nIf you believe the death of a family member was the result of a wrongful death, you should contact AziziPersonalInjury.com for an experienced personal injury lawyer who can provide action equal to his caring. Expert, qualified legal representation and assistance can help you receive just compensation for your loss, and your taking that action helps overcome your sense of helplessness. An initial consultation where we can discuss your case, which we provide at no cost or obligation, will let you know if you have grounds for legal redress and compensation and how we can best provide assistance.\n\nOur experience with similar cases gives us an advantage over some other personal injury lawyers. We know how to build and present a solid case that will give you the highest possible settlement, one that includes acknowledgment of your grief, pain and suffering, and financial consequences.\n\nWe can make sure that your loss is not any greater than it needs to be and that your unnecessary and deep pain, anguish, and loss is acknowledged and fully addressed. Nothing can replace the lost person or undo the needless death, but we can make sure your suffering stops there.', 'Wrongful Death', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '162-revision', '', '', '2013-04-30 07:03:34', '2013-04-30 07:03:34', '', 162, 'http://azizipersonalinjury.com/dev/espanol/162-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES(164, 1, '2013-04-30 06:48:04', '2013-04-30 06:48:04', '<h1>Construction / On-the-Job Accidents</h1>\r\nMost people who are involved in a construction accident or other type of on-the-job accident pursue worker’s compensation benefits to manage health and medical costs. However, if you are injured on the job because of employer negligence or the negligence of someone else, you may be entitled to receive additional compensation. The Law Office of David Azizi has worked with many clients who have successfully filed a negligence claim against their employer and other offending parties. Our team of personal injury lawyers can help you obtain a fair compensation for your specific case. \r\n\r\n<h3>Working with Construction Accident Lawyers <h3>\r\n\r\nConstruction accident lawyers specialize in specific work injuries related to working on a construction project or in the field. Common types of construction accidents include:\r\nCommercial trucking accidents\r\nForklift injuries\r\nOSHA violations\r\nChemical exposure\r\nChemical burns\r\nFalls that cause extensive injury\r\n\r\nIf you are a victim of any of these types of accidents, you may be eligible to receive monetary compensation and benefits beyond worker’s compensation from your employer. \r\n\r\n<h3>Legal Representation for On-the-Job Accidents </h3>\r\n\r\nOn-the-job accidents that result in catastrophic injury or illness will also require formal legal representation from an experienced personal injury attorney. You may need the assistance of personal injury lawyers from AziziPersonalInjyry.com if you are suffering from on-the-job accidents injuries. The common types of on-the-job accident injuries include:\r\nNeurological disorders\r\nSpinal cord injury\r\nBrain injury\r\nAccidental amputation\r\nSevere burns\r\nIllnesses that affect the central nervous system\r\nLoss of movement\r\nCognitive impairment\r\n\r\nAlmost any type of accident can result in short-term and long-term injuries that may require ongoing physician care and other forms of medical care to help an injured client recover from his/her injuries. In many cases, this type of extended care is not covered in a workers’ compensation benefits package so you will need to file an additional claim to receive compensation for all damages incurred. \r\n\r\nOur firm offers a number of services to help you build a strong case for your claim and receive appropriate compensation you deserve. We understand how challenging it can be to work with insurance companies who want a quick settlement so they pay only a fraction of the medical expenses related to your care. At AziziPersonalInjury.com, we take extra steps to protect all of your legal rights and help you receive appropriate compensation. \r\n\r\nWe will not charge you a single dollar until your case is resolved and will do everything legally possible to pursue your case as thoroughly as possible. Contact us today for a free, no obligation consultation so we can provide you immediate assistance in filing your claim or lawsuit.', 'Construction Accidents', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '131-revision-3', '', '', '2013-04-30 06:48:04', '2013-04-30 06:48:04', '', 131, 'http://azizipersonalinjury.com/dev/espanol/131-revision-3/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES(165, 1, '2013-04-30 06:37:22', '2013-04-30 06:37:22', '<h1>Bicycle and Bike Accidents</h1>\r\nAlmost every Vehicle Code in the country states that bicyclists have the same rights and responsibilities as a driver of a motor vehicle. However, many motorists do not realize how easy it is to run into a bicyclist. Bicycle accidents can occur at any time. The majority of bicycle accidents occur in a bike lane, crosswalk, or when a car or truck makes a turn without checking their blind spot. A bicycle accident or a bicycle-car crash can be serious and you will need the advice of an experienced bicycle accident lawyer from the Law Office of David Azizi. \r\n\r\n<h3>Why Do You Need a Personal Injury Lawyer for a Bicycle Accident?</h3>\r\n\r\nAWhen you have been badly injured as a result of a bicycle accident, you need the assistance of a personal injury lawyer to help you receive the compensation you deserve for damages you have sustained. While some people suffer serious injuries at the scene of the accident, many suffer from ongoing pain and health problems weeks, even months after the bike accident occurred. In all of these cases, a personal injury attorney from the Law Offices of David Azizi can help you receive the appropriate compensation you deserve. \r\n\r\nA bicycle or bike accident can produce serious injuries, and you may need the assistance of an experienced personal injury attorney to receive full compensation for any lost wages, medical expenses and other related costs. The professionals at AziziPersonalInjury.com specialize in road accidents case \r\n\r\nYou need the assistance of a strong and experienced attorney to present your case after a bicycle accident, and we will always look out for your best interests.\r\n\r\n<h3>How Azizi Personal Injury Will Manage Your Bike Accident Case</h3>\r\n\r\nOur firm gets involved in building a solid case by reviewing police reports, interviewing witnesses, conducting scene investigations, retaining the appropriate experts, and conducting the necessary discovery. Even though you can manage these tasks on your own, our experienced attorneys can speed up the process and make sure all of the facts surrounding your case are covered. \r\n\r\nContact us as soon as possible so we can take a close look at your case ad to help you get started on a successful recovery. Bicycle and bike accidents can take their toll on your physical and emotional health for several years after the event, so it’s important to work with an experienced personal injury attorney from the Law Offices of David Azizi. ', 'Bicycle and Bike Accidents', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '114-revision-2', '', '', '2013-04-30 06:37:22', '2013-04-30 06:37:22', '', 114, 'http://azizipersonalinjury.com/dev/espanol/114-revision-2/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
