INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES(270, 1, '2013-05-11 02:12:36', '2013-05-11 02:12:36', '<h1>Herida de Médula Espinal</h1>\n\nUna herida de la médula espinal puede ser físicamente, financieramente y emocionalmente una experiencia muy estresante . Las víctimas de una herida espinal a menudo sufren de los efectos secundario de la herida durante anos, abeces asta décadas, y la carga financiera de gastos médicos progresivos, incapacidad para trabajar, y la responsabilidad de pagar por rehabilitación física puede ser estresante. Las Oficinas de Ley de David Aziz puede reducir el estres de manejar su caso de heridas de médula espinal desarrollando un caso fuerte contra el partido negligente. \n\nTenemos experiencia extensa en la ley personal de heridas, y nos dedicados en asegurarnos que reciba la compensación maxima que usted merece.  \n\n<h3>Tipos de Heridas de Médula Espinal</h3>\n\nLas heridas de la médula espinal toman típicamente la forma de un disco herniado en la columna vertebral, heridas torácicas y síndrome central de cuerda. La mayoría de las heridas de atrás son el resultado de un accidente de auto, choque de camión, un accidente de construcción donde los huesos de espalda de la victima se llegan a ser separados o en casos más severos, roto. Los tipos más comunes de heridas de médula espinal incluyen:\nheridas de disco herniado-también conocido como un disco abultado o disco reventado, este tipo de herida de médula espinal ocurre típicamente cuando el peque o hueso conectado a la espina dorsal separa los huesos de atrás humanos y crea presión en la columna vertebral. Los efectos de este tipo de herida incluyen dolor de hombro, dolor de pierna y dolor de parte inferior de la espalda.\nAtorácico de heridas -estas heridas son sostenidas en el área abdominal de músculo y tienen como resultado paraplejía. Esto significa que el individuo típicamente no puede mover las piernas ni los pies a consecuencia del impacto violento a la espina dorsal.\nEl síndrome central de la cuerda - esto es una herida incompleta de médula espinal que tiene como resultado el deterioro de los armamentos y manos. El dano ocurre típicamente en las regiones superiores de la médula espinal y a menudo lleva a extensa pérdida sensoria.\n\nUna herida de la médula espinal puede ser grave e incluso le puede costar la vida. Si usted fue involucrado en un accidente que causó herida a su espina dorsal, contacta las Oficinas de Ley de David Azizi para que podamos evaluar su caso gratis.  \n\n<h3>Trabajar con un Abogado de Herida de Médula Espinal </h3>\n\nAziziPersonalInjury.com has extensive experience in litigating spinal cord injury cases. We can help you recover appropriate compensation for your damages which you deserve that were caused by the traumatic event. Unfortunately, many insurance companies will try to reduce the gravity of the situation and reach a quick settlement; however, this does not take your best interests into account, and you may end up paying far more out-of-pocket expenses than you should. \n\nOur firm is dedicated to making sure you receive adequate compensation for your damages related to your spinal cord injury case. We will litigate your case using all of our resources and years of expertise in the field. We will determine your actual medical condition, find out how long your injuries will cause pain and suffering, and determine what your work-related needs and expenses may be. These details will need to be included in your settlement, and you can count on us to help you every step of the way. \n\nContact us today for a free, no obligation consultation and find out how we can help you receive the full compensation you deserve from your spinal injury case.', 'Herida de Médula Espinal', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '154-autosave', '', '', '2013-05-11 02:12:36', '2013-05-11 02:12:36', '', 154, 'http://azizipersonalinjury.com/dev/espanol/154-autosave/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES(271, 1, '2013-04-30 07:09:29', '2013-04-30 07:09:29', '<h1>Spinal Cord Injury</h1>\r\nA spinal cord injury can be a physically, emotionally and financially devastating experience. Victims of a spinal injury often suffer from the side effects of the injury for years, even decades, and the financial burden of ongoing medical expenses, the inability to work, and the responsibility to pay for physical rehabilitation can be stressful. The Law Office of David Aziz can reduce the stress of handling spinal cord injuries by developing a strong case against the negligent party. We have extensive experience in personal injury law, and are dedicated to making sure you receive the full compensation you deserve. \r\n\r\n<h3>Types of Spinal Cord Injuries </h3>\r\n\r\nSpinal cord injuries typically take the form of a herniated disc in the spinal column, thoracic injuries and central cord syndrome. Most back injuries are the result of an auto accident, truck crash a construction accident where the victim’s back bones become separated or in more severe cases, broken. The most common types of spinal cord injuries include:\r\nHerniated disc injuries – also known as a bulging disc or ruptured disc, this type of spinal cord injury typically occurs when the small bone connected to the spine separates the human back bones and creates pressure on the spinal column. The effects of this type of injury include shoulder pain, leg pain and lower back pain.\r\nThoracic injuries – these injuries are sustained in the abdominal muscle area and result in paraplegia. This means the individual typically cannot move their legs or feet as a result of the violent impact to the spine.\r\nCentral cord syndrome - this is an incomplete spinal cord injury that results in the impairment of the arms and hands. The damage typically occurs in the upper regions of the spinal cord and often leads to extensive sensory loss.\r\n\r\nA spinal cord injury can be serious and even life threatening. If you were involved in an accident that caused injury to your spine, contact the Law Offices of David Azizi so that we may provide a free evaluation of your claim. \r\n\r\n<h3>Working with a Spinal Cord Injury Lawyer </h3>\r\n\r\nAziziPersonalInjury.com has extensive experience in litigating spinal cord injury cases. We can help you recover appropriate compensation for your damages which you deserve that were caused by the traumatic event. Unfortunately, many insurance companies will try to reduce the gravity of the situation and reach a quick settlement; however, this does not take your best interests into account, and you may end up paying far more out-of-pocket expenses than you should. \r\n\r\nOur firm is dedicated to making sure you receive adequate compensation for your damages related to your spinal cord injury case. We will litigate your case using all of our resources and years of expertise in the field. We will determine your actual medical condition, find out how long your injuries will cause pain and suffering, and determine what your work-related needs and expenses may be. These details will need to be included in your settlement, and you can count on us to help you every step of the way. \r\n\r\nContact us today for a free, no obligation consultation and find out how we can help you receive the full compensation you deserve from your spinal injury case.', 'Spinal Cord Injuries', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '154-revision-3', '', '', '2013-04-30 07:09:29', '2013-04-30 07:09:29', '', 154, 'http://azizipersonalinjury.com/dev/espanol/154-revision-3/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES(272, 1, '2013-05-11 02:13:55', '2013-05-11 02:13:55', '<h1>Accidentes de Tren</h1>\n\nSi usted ha participado en un accidente de cruce de ferrocarril, un choque de tren o choque de automóvil-tren, usted necesitará la ayuda de un abogado de accidente de tren para representarlo en su caso. El transporte del tren continúa de ser uno de los métodos más populares de transporte y envío, especialmente en Los Angeles y la comunidad circundante. Sin embargo, accidentes de tren de California han llegado a ser más comunes porque más personas viajan en tren y para el transporte diario. \n\nLos abogados de Las Oficinas de Ley de David Azizi tienen experiencia extensa en representar a clientes que han sufrido accidentes de tren y heridas que resulta de un choque de tren. \n\n<h3>Las Causas comunes de Accidentes de Tren </h3>\n\nLas causas más comunes de accidentes de tren incluyen:\nDescarrilamientos\nTrenes con otros treness\nTrenes con coches\nAccidentes adentro del Tren\nFracaso mecánico\n\nEl accidente también puede ser el resultado de varias negligencia de acontecimientos como conductor, cruces sin marcar de ferrocarril, equipo mal mantenido de ferrocarril o fatiga de conductor. Sin embargo, todos trenes son gobernados por leyes de Estado y usted necesitará representación legal formal. \n\n<h3>Common Injuries Sustained from a Train Accident </h3>\n\nA personal injury lawyer can help you receive compensation for damages as a result of injuries from the accident. The most common injuries that occur from a train accident include:\nBrain injury\nSpinal cord injuries\nJoint or muscle pain that requres medical care/rehabilitation\nMigraines and headaches\nBurn injuries\n\n<h3>Working with a Train Accident Lawyer </h3>\n\nAn experienced train accident lawyer from AziziPersonalInjury.com will determine the scope of your case and outline all damages incurred both directly and indirectly from the accident. Train accident lawyers at AziziPersonalInjury.com